  "content": "span class=\"highlight-amber\">Beautiful Code.</span><br>\n    So What's Wrong?\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\">\n    I've been using Claude Code to build visual outputs &mdash;<br>\n    LinkedIn carousels, a VS Code dashboard, brand guidelines.\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"flex: 1; margin-bottom: 0; border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-blue); text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">&#128196;</div>\n      <h3 style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--accent-blue); margin-bottom: 8px;\">Carousels</h3>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5;\">\n        PDF slides with<br>charts &amp; diagrams\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"flex: 1; margin-bottom: 0; border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-purple); text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">&#128187;</div>\n      <h3 style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--accent-purple); margin-bottom: 8px;\">Dashboard</h3>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5;\">\n        React + TypeScript<br>multi-panel layout\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"card\" style=\"flex: 1; margin-bottom: 0; border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-amber); text-align: center;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 36px; margin-bottom: 12px;\">&#127912;</div>\n      <h3 style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--accent-amber); margin-bottom: 8px;\">Brand Guide</h3>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5;\">\n        Color, typography,<br>logo placement\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-green);\">\n    <div class=\"card-header\" style=\"color: var(--accent-green);\">What AI does well</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.6;\">\n      Understands flexbox, grid, CSS variables. Writes clean HTML.\n      <strong>Technically fluent.</strong>\n    </div>\n  </div>",
